author: The Press-Enterprise
title: LOCAL COLLEGES: UCR women beat LB State in soccer
text:
staff reports
Published: Oct. 16, 2015 Updated: 11:27 p.m. The UC Riverside women’s soccer team handed Long Beach State its first Big West Conference loss on Friday night with 2-1 decision at the 49ers home field.
Blanca Barrio scored both times for the Highlanders to bring her total goals to five on the season.
Barrio was assisted by Brittany Mata in the 22nd minute and scored again unassisted in the 49th minute.
Mimi Rangel scored on a penalty kick in the 71st minute for the 49ers (8-4-3, 3-1) who outshot the Highlanders, 13-7.
Elizabeth Silas made four saves for UCR (9-6, 3-1).
MORE WOMEN’S SOCCER
MSJC 16, Imperial Valley 0: Patricia Roach led the Eagles (10-2 5-1) with two goals and three assists against the visiting Arabs (0-10) in a Pacific Coast Conference match.
SBVC 3, Rio Hondo 1: Baylee Williams scored two second-half goals for the Wolverines (12-1-2, 3-0 Foothill Conference) against the visiting Road-runners (9-1-2, 1-1).
The Wolverines were given their third goal on an own-goal by the Roadrunners.
Fullerton 4, Norco 0: The Mustangs (2-11, 0-9) fell to the host Hornets (5-7-2, 4-4-1) in an Orange Empire Conference match.
MEN’S SOCCER
Norco 2, Cypress 1: The Mustangs (3-8-1, 1-5) defeated the host Chargers (3-9-1, 1-6) on a goal by Francisco Bautista in the 89th minute of their OEC match.
SBVC 2, Rio Hondo 0: Bryan Oropeza and Aldo Iniguez each scored for the Wolverines (5-4-6, 2-1) to pick up a Foothill Conference victory at home.
Danny Meza assisted on Oropeza’s goal in the 57th minute. Iniguez scored unassisted 20 minutes later.
